[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three injured in car crash on Glasgow's Argyle Street

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three people have been taken to hospital after three cars crashed on a busy road in Glasgow's west end.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The collision happened at about 16:50 on Monday near the Kelvin Hall, close to where Argyle Street becomes Dumbarton Road.
It involved an Audi and a Nissan with a third car then being struck.
Two people who were travelling in the Nissan were taken by ambulance to New South Glasgow University Hospital where their injuries were said to be serious.
A third person was also taken to hospital for treatment to minor leg injuries.
The road was closed in both directions for several hours while an investigation was carried out.
